# --- Database (Supabase-hosted Postgres) ---
# From Supabase: click the green "Connect" button (top of dashboard) → ORMs → Prisma.
# Supabase gives you TWO strings — you need both:
# DATABASE_URL = pooled connection, used for normal app queries at runtime
# DIRECT_URL   = direct connection, used only when running `prisma db push` / `migrate`
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.xxxxx:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-xxxxx.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.xxxxx:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-xxxxx.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres"

# --- NextAuth ---
# Generate with: npx auth secret
AUTH_SECRET="replace-with-a-random-32-byte-secret"
AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# --- Cloudinary (medicine images, company logos, gallery) ---
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=""
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=""
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=""
